definitions.definition: Of, containing, or being a notion ; mental or imaginary .
examples: The idea that a rooster says cock-a-doodle-doo rather than ooh ooh-ooh ooh-ooh is socially conventional even though its sound correspondence is at heart notional .

definitions.definition: Speculative, theoretical, not the result of research.
examples: This paper proposes a notional Federated Identity Management (FIM) architecture.

definitions.definition: Having descriptive value as opposed to a syntactic category .
Used to indicate an estimate or a reference amount
